      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OUI FLOURISH (7) drifted back further back than anticipated with a disappointing seventh over 1400m at Kembla Grange in similar company. Assess on her excellent third at Warwick Farm two-starts back in BM72 class. Tempo suits and no shock to see her return to winning form. AUSBRED HED'N'TAIL (3) justified the heavy support on debut ($1.85 fav), with a slick on pace Maiden win over 1200m at Gosford. Berry sticks from the good gate and has the upside to win again. CLASSIC POCKET (2) trained locally and comes here in peak condition fourth-up. Closed strongly with a tidy third over 1200m at Gosford in this class. Each way. THE MAGIC MAN (5) big improver second-up with a determined Maiden win over 1200m at Newcastle from the sticky gate. Minor chance.",
